** We are unique **

  

Join an organisation that values your voice, empowers your autonomy,
recognises the strength in diversity, and prioritises your well-being while
offering attractive remuneration and benefits. Take pride in having a
meaningful impact on regional, rural and remote communities while being a
pivotal player in the energy industry's future.

** About the role **

  

We currently have opportunities in our 2025 Graduate Program in the
disciplines of Business, Commerce, Economics, Data, Sustainability, Health
Science, Human Resources and Information Technology. The specific roles
include:

  

_ ** Business, Commerce and Economics: ** _

  

** Business Change Graduate ** \- _ _ Bachelor of Business or Commerce _ \- Gain a well-rounded understanding of how business change, you'll play an important role in supporting the delivery of projects and change in Essential Energy. This role will provide you with the support, learning opportunities, and hands-on experience necessary to embark on a rewarding and successful career in project management, change management or audit. _

_ ** Contract management Graduate - ** _ Bachelor of Business or Commerce _ \-
Collaborate with other stakeholders to ensure outcomes are achieved in
compliance with relevant legislation and policy and the opportunity to build
and maintaining relationships, giving you the opportunity to expand your
skills in Contract Management. _

_ ** Commercial Development Graduate - ** _ Bachelor of Business or Commerce
or Economics _ \- Commercialise and develop our wireless and fibre
telecommunication assets with access to safe, fast reliable telecommunications
by realising the full potential of our network infrastructure. Be part of a
group that not only excels in technical proficiency but also makes a real
difference in the world by enhancing the connectivity and resilience of our
Essential Energy network. _

  

_ ** Data: ** _

  

_ ** Data Graduate - ** _ Bachelor of Data Science, Computer Science,
Information Technology, Mathematics, Machine Learning Engineering - _ Join a
team that works right across the organisation, becoming recognised as a data
expert, having a direct impact on driving the optimisation and improvement of
product development and helping to build and construct sophisticated data
processing pipelines, amongst other things. _

  

_ ** Sustainability: ** _

  

_ ** Sustainability Graduate - ** _ Bachelor of Sustainability, Bachelor of
Business, Bachelor of Engineering or Bachelor of Environmental Science - _
collaborating and liaising with internal and external stockholders and helping
to develop and implement sustainability initiatives, as well as assisting with
sustainability data management, governance, reporting and communications. _

  

_ ** Health Science: ** _

  

_ ** Health Science Graduate - ** _ ** ** Bachelor of Health Sciences or
Bachelor of Occupational Therapy or Bachelor of Physiotherapy - _ Work closely
with a variety of people and departments within Essential Energy, with no two
days being the same. _ _ Gain experience in support with injury and illness
case management, assist with Health Program delivery and managing Workers
Compensation processes, giving you the ability to develop your expertise with
the opportunity for career growth and development in the future. _

  

_ ** Human Resources: ** _

  

** Human Resources Graduate ** \- Bachelor of Business (major in Human Resources) _ \- _ Influence and shape our organisation's culture by working on Human Resources initiatives and supporting our business across the spectrum of People and Safety. 

  
  

** About You **

  

You are passionate about what you do and are excited to grow your career with
a supportive and inclusive team, where you will have the opportunity to push
boundaries to create innovative solutions to real world problems, all while
making positive contributions to the community.

  

